##  Reflection

Would it be helpful or burdensome to apply PCI-style strict requirements to OpenMRS?  
Personally, I believe many healthcare orgs *would benefit* from more explicit security checklists â€” especially those new to HIPAA or without strong internal security maturity.  

> â€œCompliance isnâ€™t security â€” but it can drive foundational improvements.â€  

And I would advocate for applying **PCI DSS-like rigor** to critical healthcare systems â€” because at the end of the day: **PHI is just as sensitive â€” if not more â€” than payment data.**

